properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 8 at 9:01AM AKST by NWS Anchorage AK
properties.description:
Water is still reported to be flowing over the Deneki Road as a
result of a freeze up ice jam on Willow Creek upstream of the Deneki
Road bridge. The initial ice jam and rapid rise in water levels at
the Deneki Bridge occurred on December 21st. The ice jam forced
water into the floodplain on both the North and South sides of the
river. Water levels have fluctuated over the last two weeks and are
expected to continue to fluctuate as the river continues the normal
freeze-up process.

The ice jam is not expected to release until spring break-up.
Once the river upstream forms an ice cover water levels are
expected to decrease, but the ice jam rubble will remain in place
upstream of the bridge. Areas of standing water will likely freeze
with forecast cold temperatures over the next one to two weeks.

The Matanuska Borough has been responding to the flooding on
Willow Creek and maintains a website for updated information on
road conditions and access. Please check this website for current
updates on the conditions near Deneki Road:
https://www.matsugov.us/spotlights/willow-creke-flooding-2019

The Borough has also been posting updates to their Facebook page:
https://www.facebook.com/MatSuBorough

NWSheadline: ICE JAM FLOODING CONTINUES ON WILLOW CREEK UPSTREAM OF THE DENEKI ROAD BRIDGE
